8.21	Into_the_Wild_(book)	Into the Wild (book)	Into the Wild is a 1996 non-fiction book written by Jon Krakauer. It is an expansion of Krakauer's 9,000-word article on Christopher McCandless entitled "Death of an Innocent", which appeared in the January 1993 issue of Outside. The book was adapted into a 2007 movie of the same name directed by Sean Penn with Emile Hirsch starring as McCandless.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/63/Into_the_Wild_%28book%29_cover.png/200px-Into_the_Wild_%28book%29_cover.png
